+Now, create a new file `indexing/indexer.py`. This script will be our main pipeline to scan the project directory. 
+It should:
+1. Walk through the project directory (ignoring `.venv`, `.git`, `.aider*`, `__pycache__`, and `todos.json`).
+2. Read all `.py` and `.txt` files.
+3. Split the code/text into smaller chunks (e.g., functions, classes, or 500-character blocks).
+4. For each chunk, call `get_embedding(chunk)` from `llm/embedding.py`.
+5. Store the file_path, line_number, chunk_text, and embedding using `indexing/vector_store.py`.
+6. Save everything into a single `memory/brain.json` file.
